feature_description: Create FixtureRegistry class for managing fixture definitions. Include: 1) register(definition: FixtureDefinition) method to add fixtures, 2) get(name: str) -> FixtureDefinition method for lookup, 3) has(name: str) -> bool method to check existence, 4) list_all() -> list[FixtureDefinition] to list registered fixtures, 5) clear() method to reset registry. Should detect duplicate registrations and raise appropriate errors. Build on existing FixtureDefinition from quaestor/testing/fixtures.py. Do NOT implement dependency resolution or scope management.
